                        <collation>
                           <p>
									28 complete quires: i-xvi8 (folios 2-209), separate folio 210, xxvii-xviii6 (folios 219-230), folios 231-234 (additions). 
									Quires enumerated with Hebrew letters, cut away in the trimming. 
								</p>
                        </collation>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <p>Columns: 2;
                                                  ruled lines: 35;
                                                  written lines: 34; Uniform layout. Visible quire by quire pricking and page by page (brown) plummet ruling, also for the margins. Commentary in a small semi-cursive script provided around the main text. Last line of writing written within the ruling. Hair side and flesh side of folios distinguishable. Occasionally additional notes. Repeated words at the beginning of columns. Decorated horizontal catchwords. </p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <scriptDesc>
                     <scriptNote>Ashkenazi square and semi-cursive script of the 14th century. Shemayah: inscribed with his name in the colophon, folio 210v. Written for Mosheh ben Yosef: inscribed, folio 210. </scriptNote>
                  </scriptDesc>
